# Suits Cashier Backend

Node.js **ESM** (`"type": "module"`) Express API for a suits cashier app. MongoDB via Mongoose. Entrypoint: `index.js` → `src/app.router.js`.

## Layout

- `src/modules/<Feature>/` — routes, controller, validation per feature
- `src/middleware/` — shared middleware (auth, generic validation)
- `src/utils/` — `ErrorCatch`, uploads (`multer`), Redis helpers
- `DB/<Entity>/` — Mongoose models (e.g. `Users.js`, `Orders.model.js`)
- `uploads/` — static files served at `/uploads`

## Stack

- Express 4, Mongoose 8, Joi, JWT, argon2, multer, sharp, dotenv, cors
- Optional Redis (`src/utils/redis.js`) — degrade gracefully if unavailable

## Conventions

- Prefer **named exports** for controllers/middleware; **default export** for routers
- Use relative `.js` import paths (ESM)
- Register new feature routers in `src/app.router.js`
- Keep secrets in `.env` only — never hardcode JWT secrets or DB credentials
- Match existing response shape: `{ success, message, ...data }`
